  "section": "Math",
  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Substitute both expressions",
      "content": "Use $p=4x+3$ and $v=x+6$ in $pv-2p+v$:<br/>$$(4x+3)(x+6)-2(4x+3)+(x+6)$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Expand the product",
      "content": "First expand and distribute:<br/>$$(4x+3)(x+6)=4x^2+27x+18$$<br/>$$-2(4x+3)=-8x-6$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Combine like terms",
      "content": "Now combine all three parts:<br/>$$4x^2+27x+18-8x-6+x+6=4x^2+20x+18$$The answer is <strong>B</strong>."
    }
  ]
}
